rComments: Clarissa is an engaging, and well-prepared lecturer. I found her to be very kind, intelligent, & down-to-earth. She is up-to-date on the newest ethical guidelines in Canada. I had two conferences to present at this term that overlapped, and she was very accommodating. I wish I could write more. Highly recommend! Superb professor and person. +++++

Lectures are long  dry. In this class you are assigned debate topics. Beware of getting the debate topic that goes against her personal opinions because if you do a good job arguing for it, you will be scolded in class. Very old school too - teaches ethics using terms like "Thou shall" "Thou must" and "Thou may".  Get another prof if you can.
